name: The Apprentice movie
summary: Multiple news articles have emerged surrounding the release of "The Apprentice," a biopic about Donald Trump's early years featuring Sebastian Stan and Jeremy Strong. The film has sparked controversy, with Trump's campaign calling its premiere at Cannes "blatantly false." Dan Snyder, a billionaire investor, is reportedly furious with Trump's portrayal in the movie, which he believed would be more flattering. Reviews have been mixed, with some praising Stan and Strong's performances while others criticize the film's depiction of Trump's character. The Guardian has described it as a "cartoon version" of Trump's early years, while The Telegraph has labeled it "a sleaze-slathered look" at his rise to power.

name: Anthony Edwards
summary: Anthony Edwards, the young star of the Minnesota Timberwolves, has made waves in the NBA with his impressive performances. In their Game 7 victory against the Denver Nuggets, Edwards overcame a poor start to lead his team to victory, further solidifying his status as a rising superstar. His accomplishments at age 22 have drawn comparisons to legends like Kobe Bryant, LeBron James, and Steph Curry. Edwards has been vocal both on and off the court, inviting Charles Barkley to visit Minneapolis and criticizing Jamal Murray for trash-talking to Mike Conley. His unique catchphrase, "Bring ya a**," has become a beloved slogan in Minnesota and has even been adopted by the state's tourism campaign. Edwards' girlfriend's outfit choice at a playoff game also gained attention, while fellow NBA star Ja Morant sent him a message of respect.

summary: The Indiana Pacers forced a Game 7 in their NBA playoff series against the New York Knicks after a convincing victory in Game 6. The Knicks are now tasked with winning in Indiana to advance to the Eastern Conference Finals for the first time in 24 years. The Pacers set a playoff record with their shooting in Game 7, outscoring the Knicks by 30 points. The Knicks will aim to hold home court advantage in Game 7 and clinch the series. Experts predict a close matchup, with the Knicks favored by a slight margin. The game will be broadcast on various channels and streaming services. The Pacers' impressive performance in Game 7 was fueled by the fiery coaching of Rick Carlisle, who pushed his team to a record-breaking shooting display.

name: Red Lobster
summary: Red Lobster, the seafood restaurant chain, has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. The move comes amid declining sales and competition from other casual dining chains. As part of the bankruptcy proceedings, Red Lobster has closed several locations across the United States, including four in Maryland, one in Silver Spring, and several in New Jersey and Texas. Despite the bankruptcy filing, Red Lobster's restaurants will remain open while the chain reorganizes its finances. Analysts have cited various factors contributing to Red Lobster's struggles, including the company's debt load, its reliance on Endless Shrimp promotions, and broader industry trends.

name: ICC
summary: Multiple news sources report that the International Criminal Court (ICC) prosecutor has requested arrest warrants for senior Israeli and Hamas officials, including Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar. The warrants are sought in connection with alleged war crimes committed during the 2014 Gaza conflict. The United States has expressed opposition to the move, while experts analyze the potential implications of the ICC's actions and the unprecedented targeting of a U.S. ally. Organizations like Amnesty International and the Financial Times have weighed in, supporting the ICC's efforts to hold accountable those responsible for serious crimes. The developments highlight ongoing tensions and debate surrounding international justice and accountability for human rights violations.

name: Woo
summary: Bryan Woo, a promising pitcher for the Seattle Mariners, made an impressive debut start, striking out five batters and contributing to the team's victory. Pulitzer Prize winner Ilyon Woo shared insights from the late filmmaker Dai Sil Kim Gibson's craft. Golfer Min Woo Lee made three dramatic chip-ins to ascend the leaderboard at the PGA Championship. Director Woo Ming Jin completed "The Fox King," a telepathic twins film that won at Locarno. In Seattle, an ethics official recommended recusal for a city council member in a minimum wage vote. Bryan Woo's stellar pitching performance boosted the Mariners to victory over the Royals. Netflix announced a romantic comedy titled "All The Love You Wish For" featuring Kim Woo-bin. Additionally, an e-flux announcement highlighted an exhibition featuring artworks by Miguel Ángel Payano Jr. and Liang Hao.
